          "chunk_id": "3b1cb956-a302-551d-b204-077761b56c12",
          "page_number": 1,
          "section_heading": "METHODS",
          "text": "METHODS\n\nThe prototype used a six-axis IMU mounted on the shank and sampled motion at 100 Hz. A\nforce-sensitive resistor under the heel recorded foot contact."
        },
        {
          "chunk_id": "c90a4e50-36b2-5ba7-85aa-467fb583db26",
          "page_number": 2,
          "section_heading": "RESULTS",
          "text": "RESULTS\n\nTen healthy volunteers completed the walking protocol. Mean step-count error was 3.2\npercent, and measured battery life was 6 hours."
        }
      ],
      "display_title": "Wearable Rehabilitation Prototype",
      "document_id": "af9b1f25-2aa2-5797-b41f-cc986f0f6204",
      "file_name": "wearable_rehabilitation.pdf",
      "sha256": "3e2e1b334040667894ab9b33f44b59719c9aa620f4b8dd8a25675d42db22f86b"
    },
    {
      "chunks": [
        {
          "chunk_id": "2110eaae-7646-5ec9-8a88-ddb0ce2b98db",
          "page_number": 1,
          "section_heading": "SAFETY",
          "text": "SAFETY\n\nThe device is intended for supervised rehabilitation research and is not a diagnostic device.\nStop use if skin irritation or pain occurs."
        },
        {
          "chunk_id": "dd1f62c2-841d-5afd-9aef-deeb0a56f178",
          "page_number": 2,
          "section_heading": "CALIBRATION",
          "text": "CALIBRATION\n\nCalibrate the IMU while stationary for 10 seconds. Zero the force-sensitive resistor with no\nload before each session."
        }
      ],
      "display_title": "Rehabilitation Device Safety Guidance",
      "document_id": "3e2c998b-7a69-5ad2-9efe-a2e5b010cba7",
